    "causal_summary": "Phase 011 asked for a dead-PID liveness probe, but that read-path probe already exists in `lease.ts:226-247`. The remaining gap is acquisition-time reclaim: `lease.ts:300-317` reads an existing row, evaluates staleness/liveness, then writes a new lease. That probe-then-set sequence is not atomic, so two launchers can race on the same stale row.",
